{"title_page": "Tigers (film)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Tigers\n| image          = Tigers Film.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Danis Tanovic]]\n| producer       = Prashita Chaudhary<br />Kshitij Chaudhary<br />Guneet Monga<br />[[Anurag Kashyap]]<br />Cedomir Kolar<br />Marc Baschet<br />Andy Paterson<br />Cat Villiers<ref name=ti>{{cite web | title =  Tigers |work=TIFF| url = http://www.tiff.net/festivals/thefestival/programmes/contemporary-world-cinema/tigers | accessdate = 2014-10-20 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821060947/http://www.tiff.net/festivals/thefestival/programmes/contemporary-world-cinema/tigers|archivedate=21 August 2014}}</ref>\n| screenplay     = [[Danis Tanovic]]<br />[[Andy Paterson]]\n| story          = [[Danis Tanovic]]\n| starring       = [[Emraan Hashmi]]<br />[[Khalid Abdalla]]<br />[[Geetanjali Thapa]]<br />[[Supriya Pathak]]\n| music          = [[JAM8]]\n| cinematography = Erol Zubcevic\n| editing        = Prerna Saigal\n| studio         = [[Sikhya Entertainment]]<br />A.S.A.P. Films\n| distributor    = [[ZEE5]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2014|09|08|Toronto|2018|11|21|Digital Premiere}}\n| runtime        = 90 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Hindi]]<br />English<br />[[German language|German]]\n}}\n\n'''''Tigers''''' (initially titled ''White Lies'')<ref>{{cite news|title=Emraan Hashmi's international debut Tigers to premiere at Toronto|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/2604179/Emraan-Hashmis-international-debut-Tigers-to-premiere-at-Toronto|accessdate=12 September 2015|work=Bollywood Hungama News Network|date=23 August 2014}}</ref> is a 2014 Indian [[drama film]] directed by [[Danis Tanovic]], and produced as a joint production between Cinema Time, French production company ASAP Films and [[Sikhya Entertainment]]. Based on the [[Nestl\u00e9 boycott|Nestle Baby Milk Scandal]] in 1970\u2019s the film features [[Emraan Hashmi]] in the leading role as a pharmaceutical representative in [[Pakistan]] who discovers his new company's baby formula has killed hundreds of children, after which he begins a lone and dangerous battle against the company.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-28/news-interviews/40234176_1_emraan-hashmi-ghanchakkar-danis-tanovic If I stop taking risks, I will eventually crumble: Emraan Hashmi \u2013 Times Of India]</ref> The film began filming in 2013, and had its premiere in September 2014 at the [[2014 Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Emraan Hashmi: Right time to release 'Tigers' \u2013 Times of India|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Emraan-Hashmi-Right-time-to-release-Tigers/articleshow/47541440.cms|accessdate=10 September 2016|work=Times of India|date=4 June 2014}}</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vBLxSqteOv4 Does Justice System Work in Pakistan? Prime Time with Anis Farooqui @TAG TV]</ref>\n\nThe film faced multiple delays during its initial release. It was later released digitally on the on-demand platform [[ZEE5]] on 13 November 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.glamsham.com/en/emraan-hashmi-unveils-first-look-poster-of-tigers|title=First look poster of Emraan Hashmi's TIGERS released|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/emraan-hashmis-tigers-directed-by-oscar-winner-danis-tanovic-to-have-digital-premiere-on-21-november-5512591.html|title=Emraan Hashmi's Tigers, directed by Oscar-winner Danis Tanovic, to have digital premiere on 21 November|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/web-series/emraan-hashmi-tigers-zee5-5436096/|title=Emraan Hashmi\u2019s Tigers to premiere on ZEE5|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Emraan Hashmi]] as Ayaan <ref name=\"imdb\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3004774/fullcredits|title=Tigers (2014) - Full Cast & Crew on IMDb|publisher=IMDb.com|accessdate=2018-11-07}}</ref>\n* [[Geetanjali Thapa]] as Zainab\n* [[Danny Huston]] as Alex\n* [[Khalid Abdalla]] as Nadeem\n* [[Adil Hussain]] as Bilal\n* [[Maryam d'Abo]] as Maggie <ref>[http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/1807922/report-emraan-hashmi-gets-a-bond-gal Emraan Hashmi gets a Bond gal \u2013 Entertainment \u2013 DNA]</ref>\n* [[Satyadeep Mishra]] as Dr. Faiz\n* [[Heino Ferch]] as Robert\n* [[Sam Reid (actor)|Sam Reid]] as Frank\n* [[Supriya Pathak]] as Ayan's mother\n* [[Vinod Nagpal]] as Mustafa\n* [[Rubina (actor)|Rubina]] as Nurse\n* [[Inayat Sood]] as Nurse 1\n* [[Kanwal Baidwan]] as Nurse\n* [[Milind Raja]] as Nader\n* [[Sanjay Panchal]] as Sanjay\n* [[Zachary Coffin]] as Executive Trainer<ref name=\"imdb\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|3004774}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|tigers_2013}}\n{{Danis Tanovi\u0107}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2014 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films based on actual events]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Punjab, India]]\n[[Category:Films set in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Danis Tanovi\u0107]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Pharmaceutical industry]]\n[[Category:Urdu-language films]]\n[[Category:English-language Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films featuring songs by Pritam]]\n[[Category:ZEE5 original films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Tigers\n| image          = Tigers Film.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Danis Tanovic]]\n| producer       = Prashita Chaudhary<br />Kshitij Chaudhary<br />Guneet Monga<br />[[Anurag Kashyap]]<br />Cedomir Kolar<br />Marc Baschet<br />Andy Paterson<br />Cat Vi